company:18946", "educations/2/description": "Key concepts, strategies, and practical skills necessary for managing, owning, and operating a successful restaurant, bar, or other food and beverage business.\n\nManage business finances and key operational functions like menu design, income statement analysis, pricing, margin analysis, supply chain management, guest service processes, and employee engagement and performance.", "educations/2/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQE8SOXGRyv7LA/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1631339899678?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=XPjCUEJfiykmO9iB6jyNhXz62khd4aFQab9vo0g8SmY", "educations/2/period/endedOn/month": "8", "educations/2/period/endedOn/year": "2021", "educations/2/period/startedOn/month": "3", "educations/2/period/startedOn/year": "2019", "educations/2/subtitle": "Certificate Program, Food and Beverage Management", "educations/2/title": "Cornell University", "educations/3/companyId": "18946", "educations/3/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/school/cornell-university/", "educations/3/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:18946", "educations/3/description": "An executive leader’s credibility, authority and ability to keep a team focused and motivated are under constant scrutiny.\n\nThis executive leadership certificate enables and provides tools to build high-performing teams and become a more authentic leader. In an executive role, it’s crucial that everyone has the right blend of soft skills and a strategic mindset to achieve specific performance outcomes at the related organization.\n\nThe Executive Leadership Certificate Program provides critical skills to lead an organization to success through a series of six core courses and two electives that gives the flexibility to customize the program to independent goals.\n\n- Quality and Service Excellence\n- Leading Collaborative Teams\n- Strategic Decision Making\n- Leading With Credibility\n- Motivating People for High Performance\n- Coaching Skills for Leade