w through. Increased 2009 RevPar to 76 index, up 11 from 2008. Evaluated staffing levels and reduced overall FTE’s while enhancing established service levels and guest satisfaction. Overall guest satisfaction scores were raised to 44th overall within the company, up from 103rd. Increased associate morale through targeted associate events. Implemented and drove associate engagement through aggressive training programs and an on board process for all newly hired associates. Responsible for developing Executive Team through training, mentoring, constructive feedback and open communication.", "experiences/6/jobEndedOn": "12-2009", "experiences/6/jobLocation": "Maimi Florida South Beach", "experiences/6/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/6/jobStartedOn": "12-2008", "experiences/6/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/6/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQHZVNCUIfytag/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1719848403661/hyatt_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=CIh32kLseqFoTJWu_ZOEIHRVBs6seZJaXxakPXKQkg0", "experiences/6/title": "General Manager", "experiences/7/companyId": "76216", "experiences/7/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/7/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/noble-house-hotels-&-resorts/", "experiences/7/companyName": "The Grove Isle Hotel & Spa, Noble House Hotels & Resorts", "experiences/7/companySize": "1001-5000", "experiences/7/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:76216", "experiences/7/companyWebsite": "http://www.noblehousehotels.com/", "experiences/7/jobDescription": "Managed and directed multiple revenue centers including 500 condos and a membership base of 786. The Hotel was a 49 room luxury boutique with a Patrick McEnroe Tennis facility, 8000 square foot Spa Terre and 85 slip Marina.  Focus was on repositioning the resort to drive ADR and occupancy, creating a team driven culture, project development, training and increased customer focus.  Heavy emphasis was on guest satisfaction results with an overall satisf