d/25/public_identifier": "shacondrawest", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAJYR5EBu-bInF-qjpXWupiHzc0KlcjLIzI", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5603AQHh2JPqEXdsiQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1633156704804?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=K3uhqKZURAFKSPv-JpCR1-mFSFr_TfWkYhZn8KObPNU", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5603AQHh2JPqEXdsiQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1633156704804?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=K3uhqKZURAFKSPv-JpCR1-mFSFr_TfWkYhZn8KObPNU", "publicIdentifier": "kelsolewis", "publications/0/publishing_date": "Oct 5, 2018", "publications/0/source": "Bangladesh Monitor", "publications/0/title": "Country's economy strengthening, so is its hospitality industry: http://www.bangladeshmonitor.com.bd/hotel_and_restaurant/271/Country's-economy-strengthening,-so-is-its-hospitality-industry", "publications/1/publishing_date": "Dec 1, 2015", "publications/1/source": "The Bangladesh Monitor", "publications/1/title": "Amari Dhaka named Best Luxury Contemporary Hotel", "publications/1/url": "http://www.bangladeshmonitor.com.bd/hotel-and-restaurant/2015/12/01/4967", "publications/2/publishing_date": "Dec 1, 2015", "publications/2/source": "En Vouge New Age", "publications/2/title": "Amari Dhaka named Best Luxury Contemporary Hotel", "publications/2/url": "http://trends.newagebd.net/3947/amari-dhaka-named-best-luxury-contemporary-hotel-in-bangladesh/", "publications/3/publishing_date": "Apr 28, 2013", "publications/3/source": "Bankok Post", "publications/3/summary": "The courtyard of the resort's Rivet restaurant was converted to an exhibition hall to showcase impressive artistic creations in the realms of fashion, art, cuisine and entertainment.", "publications/3/title": "Indigo Pearl shows an eclectic", "publications/3/url": "http://www.bangkokpost.com/lifestyle/art/347385/indigo-pearl-shows-an-eclectic", "publications/4/publishing_date": "Jun 29, 2012", "publications/4/source": "The Phuket News", "publications/4/summary": "Indigo Pearl resort had the pleasure of hosting Miss World 2007 winner Zhang Zilin last week at its private pool villas, designed by the renowned Bill Bensley.", "publications/4/title": "Indigo Pearl welcomes Miss World", "publications/4/url": "http://www.thephuketnews.com/indigo-pearl-welcomes-miss-world-31720.php", "publications/5/publishing_date": "Mar 26, 2012", "publications/5/source": "Phuket Gazette", "publications/5/summary": "Tennis played well at any level is an enviable pursuit. Those with the physical skill and coordination required to spot a ball traveling in excess of 100 miles per hour, then choose a shot before returning the two and a half inch diameter projectile over a three foot obstacle and land it accurately within a 27ft by 39ft area, deserve admiration. To do it repeatedly over an hour or two requires abnormal focus, and to become a world champion simply defies belief.", "publications/5/title": "Phuket Sports: She’s ‘Dear’ to the heart of Indigo Pearl", "publications/5/url": "http://www.phuketgazette.net/archives/articles/2012/article12731.html", "publications/6/title": "Country", "recommendations/0/context": "Kelly managed Ahsanul Alam directly", "recommendations/0/date": "October 28, 2021", "recommendations/0/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Raj at Amari Hotel Dhaka, when he was my Senior FB Team Manager in Amaya.  Raj is a wealth of knowledge on everything F&B, and total complete ownership of the IT portion of the numerous F&B computer systems that we employed.  I found Raj to be a tremendous team player that worked extremely hard to ensure he and his team delivered day in and day out.  He was an excellent recruiter of talent for the restaurants in the hotel as well, getting us some of the most wonderful associates.  Raj possesses a great personality and sense of humor, critical for when the stress of the job occasionally got to us all.  I highly recommend Raj for his next role and wish him nothing but success in the future.  ", "recommendations/0/name": "Ahsanul Alam Raj", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Group F&B Consultant & Trainer (South East Asia)", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ahsanul-alam-raj-3a3a25a7/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABbBLesByU2GECSxQOgNj22vHipp6DhzHnw", "recommendations/1/context": "Kelly managed Angela directly", "recommendations/1/date": "November 10, 2013", "recommendations/1/description": "Not sure how I can put the importance of Angela's role in Indigo Pearl when I arrived half the staff could not even speak English, we decided to form a training and development  department as she had an English education back ground....all I can say is WOW...she not only set it up but trained the locals around her so they could succeed with out her, if not for her there would be know program at Indigo and never would have been she was the sole, spirit and back bone of the training that made Indigo pearls award winning staff what it is today, I look forward to the day our paths meet again.\n\nKelly Lewis\nGeneral Manager", "recommendations/1/name": "Angela Killian", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "CRM Campaign Manager", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/angelakillian/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA_ugVYBPtsYf7Qtd34Thq93gDe01isQZeM", "recommendations/2/context": "Kelly managed Steven directly", "recommendations/2/date": "November 10, 2013", "recommendations/2/description": "I have had the pleasure of working with Steven on my team for the better part of  2 years, he was an critical part of the start op team for our Bill Bensley villas which were award winning.  Given the chance I would have no hesitation hiring him again or recommending him.  He is a true gentleman and I hope our paths cross again.\n\nKelly Lewis\nGeneral Manager\nIndigo Pearl", "recommendations/2/name": "Steven Poole", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Facilities Manager at The Rhodes Trust - Oxford University", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stevenpoole/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADWAL8BiNLjb-fjy1wyRALA-lyGXh0wJMM", "recommendations/3/context": "Kelly managed Adelaide directly", "recommendations/3/date": "November 10, 2013", "recommendations/3/description": "I have had the pleasure to work with Adelaide directly for the past 2 years she was the driving force behind the Indigo Pearls award winning spa...under her direction we won \"best luxury resort spa\" and \"best design resort spa\" . her dedication to perfection and her passion for her team and the spirit for nothing but success is uncompromised. \n\nKelly Lewis\nGeneral Manager \nIndigo Pearl Resort", "recommendations/3/name": "Adelaide Castano", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Owner at Soul Phuket", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adelaide-castano-31489a17/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAODLkABwosSSi3MiK_L3pyRVhLOJrsEZTQ", "recommendations/4/context": "Kelly managed Jude directly", "recommendations/4/date": "October 31, 2012", "recommendations/4/description": "I have worked with Jude over the past year in his current role as Director of Butlers at the Five star Indigo Pearl in Phuket and must say his perspective of any challenge is exceptional and well communicated through out the division, making him very effective in his role as well as decision maker and most important a solid leader.  It has been a pleasure working with Jude as he alway's seems to inspire people around him to learn, grow, and develop into better people.  His vision, energy, initiative and creativity combined with planning, fiscal insight, operational savy and combined years of experience at world class luxury resorts make him a unique leader, capable in any hospitality environment and ready for any challenge.  His genuine passion, loyalty and commitment to the team and the task at hand are truly remarkable.\n\nKelly Lewis\nGeneral Manager\nIndigo Pearl Resort Phuket Thailand", "recommendations/4/name": "Jude Tauro", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Resort Manager | Hospitality Management Expert Operations | Guest Experience | Leadership", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jude-tauro/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAANmNkkBxNiz2DfWHEyYlGY9q4F4T-iaW7w", "recommendations/5/context": "Kelly worked with François but they were at different companies", "recommendations/5/date": "July 3, 2012", "recommendations/5/description": "I worked indirectly with Francois when he was at Banyan Tree Laguna as Area General Manager on assorted CSR projects and must say his perspective of any challenge is exceptional and well communicated, making him a very effective observer, decision maker and most important leader; it has been a pleasure to work with Francois he always seems to inspire the people around him to learn, grow, and develop into better hoteliers, restaurateurs and people. His vision, energy, initiative and creativity combined with planning, fiscal insight, operating savvyness and his years of experience at world-class luxury resorts and hotels domestically and abroad, makes him a unique leader, capable in any hospitality environment and challenge. His genuine passion, loyalty and commitment to the team and the task at hand, are remarkable. \n\nI again worked with Francois most recently on his latest project as MD at Big Waves a unique experience of Inspiration, knowledge and dedication to his passion for unique perception training, which makes him versatile and consistently delivering the highest quality results for his students, property and company. He challenged me and pushed me to become a better hotelier and was instrumental in getting me to recognize the next level of my game. I look forward to working with Francois again in the future as we encounter new and greater adventures.” July 4th, 2012", "recommendations/5/name": "François Huet", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "🎙️ Auteur du podcast Xperientiel | 🌱 Producteur de podcasts engagés | 🤝 Facilitateur de transitions écologiques et humaines", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/françois-huet-a6527a14/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALjGG0BW1l_2Bc0PwwZiXw9Ev1rD3aBFl8", "recommendations/6/context": "Kelly managed Candi directly", "recommendations/6/date": "May 8, 2012", "recommendations/6/description": "I have known Candi for a number of years dating back to my day's with Noble House Hotels and Resorts. I have depended on Candi on many occasions in the past, regionally as well as on the property level. She is astute, articulate, a quick read and a dually effective decision maker just a joy to work with. Her Vision in planning coupled with her technical ability does truely allow you to relax when systems put you in stressful situations. She shows extreme passion for what she does and is an accomplished leader in her industry and one I will recommend for years to come.”", "recommendations/6/name": "Candi Orchulek", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Regional Director of Information Technology at Noble House Hotels & Resorts", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/candiorchulek/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAO9BXQBj1ecSn2AotiCNIJxPzDX27V2P1o", "recommendations/7/context": "Kelly worked with Kerry on the same team", "recommendations/7/date": "September 1, 2011", "recommendations/7/description": "Kerry's depth of knowledge, quick perception and ability to readily identify the talent needed to execute a hotel company's strategy is among the very best I have seen in the field of International executive recruiting.  Kerry has the ability to work alongside senior level hotel executives to help them identify exactly the type of skills and profile needed to align themselves with success.  Her approach is particularly critical to the success and understanding of a General Managers placement,  perhaps more so than any other position as these hires call for experience, imagination, perseverance, leadership and communication skills which will have a lasting impact upon a hotel or hotel company's financial success.  I would highly recommend Kerry to any top Hotel executive that is looking for a new opportunity in the international market.\n\nMr. Kelly Lewis\nGeneral Manager\nIndigo Peral Resort, Phuket Thailand", "recommendations/7/name": "Kerry Healy", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Chief Commercial Officer @ Accor | Hotels, Leisure, New Business Development", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kerryhealy/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJKC7sBITpxsb1oP9WXmZ7ddDcamhtk1dk", "recommendations/8/context": "Kelly managed Matt directly", "recommendations/8/date": "February 25, 2011", "recommendations/8/description": "I had the privilage of working with Matt from his start as his front desk and reservations positions into his current role of keeping our revenue management in scope...It has been a pleasure watching Matt progress in his current crucial role and I would recommend Matt to any company that needed his expertise.\n\nKelly Lewis \nGeneral Manager\nAmara Resport and Spa", "recommendations/8/name": "Matt Thomas", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Global Pricing Director", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mpthomas1219/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAARTzoABv-N5iAJt6FrfK0gER3ghTdkXxOA", "recommendations/9/context": "Peter was senior to Kelly but didn't manage Kelly directly", "recommendations/9/date": "February 7, 2011", "recommendations/9/description": "I have known Mr. Hilary since 2008 when he was the Asset Manager for ZOM which owned Hotel Victor in South Beach.  Mr. Hilary's depth of knowledge for the Hotel/Resort business is vast on many front's.  He is astute, articulate, a quick read and a dually effective decision maker just a no nonsence individual which were all appreciated traits when turning around an asset.  I would not hesitate to recommend Peter as you will only receive extraordinary results!", "recommendations/9/name": "Peter Hilary", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Resort Management | Hotel Operations | Employee Management | Managerial/Administrative Support | Strategic Planning | Hospitality Management | Team Leadership/Training | Operational Management | Revenue Generation", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/peter-hilary-59796722/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAATE5IMBchI03m3z6T86W3SoAc-94Eve554", "recommendations/10/context": "Kelly worked with Roger but they were at different companies", "recommendations/10/date": "January 25, 2011", "recommendations/10/description": "I have known Mr. Bingham for a number of years dating back to my day's with Noble House Hotels and Resorts.  I have depended on Mr. Bingham in the past as well as this most recent search which he articulated with Prism Hotels at the Amara Resort and Spa.  He is astute, articulate, a quick read and a dually effective decision maker just a no nonsence guy.  His Vision in planning and operations does truely allow you to relax in what can be a very stressful time in ones life, he shows extreme passion for what he does.  He is an accomplished leader in the industry and one I will recommend for years to come.", "recommendations/10/name": "Roger Bingham ( 1st level 6000+)", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "President/Owner Tesla Custom Winery Tours", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rogerbingham/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADhrR0BCRdF30XTadAyMiQGbd44EQ69T0g", "recommendations/11/context": "Kelly managed Michael directly", "recommendations/11/date": "August 12, 2010", "recommendations/11/description": "I hired Michael at Makena Beach & Golf Resort. Having hired him previously, I would do so again without hesitation. I have depended on Michael’s skills and abilities even when we were not with the same company. He is astute, articulate, a quick read and dually effective decision maker and implementer; it has been a pleasure to watch Michael develop into such an accomplished leader. His vision in planning, fiscal acumen and operating savvy are well honed through his years of experience and tireless work ethic at world-class luxury resorts and hotels domestically and abroad. He is committed and loyal to the team and its mission, I trust him implicitly. Michael has proven his versatility time and time again and he can be relied upon to deliver the highest quality results. I look forward with great confidence to his continued advancement, expanding accountabilities and ultimately an accomplished leader in the industry.", "recommendations/11/name": "Michael Blaksteen", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Hotellier and Restaurateur", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/michaelblaksteen/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKifLkB7YJLIS3j04igW0hytCiFdIz0NA4", "recommendations/12/context": "Kelly managed Dan directly", "recommendations/12/date": "January 23, 2010", "recommendations/12/description": "I have known Dan since his entry into the hospitality industry and been fortunate to work with him at several properties.  Having hired him previously, I would do so again without hesitation.  I have depended on Dan’s skills and abilities even when we were not with the same company.  He is astute, articulate, a quick read and dually effective decision maker and implementer; it has been a pleasure to watch Dan develop into such an accomplished leader. His vision in planning, fiscal acumen and operating savvy are well honed through his years of experience and tireless work ethic at world-class luxury resorts and hotels domestically and abroad.  He is committed and loyal to the team and its mission, I trust him implicitly.  Dan has proven his versatility time and time again and he can be relied upon to deliver the highest quality results.   I look forward with great confidence to his continued advancement, expanding accountabilities and ultimately an accomplished leader in the industry.", "recommendations/12/name": "Dan Daughtry", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Executive Director • Vice President Food & Beverage | Ultra-Luxury Resorts & Destination Hospitality | Aspen • Hawai’i • Tahoe • International | Pre-Opening Leadership | Forbes & AAA Service Culture", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dan-daughtry-6388b79/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAG8HcwBpN5rHQ_q8Cr_4MKGoWanwVMfATI", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Steven reported directly to Kelly", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "November 11, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I had the pleasure of working under Kelly during my time at Indigo Pearl in Phuket. Kelly was very much a results-driven GM who strived to get the very best from his team members. Kelly's strong analytical, strategic and financial skills helped ensure consistant yearly growth of the resort. No doubt Kelly would be a great asset to any company and it would be a pleasure to work with him again in the future.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Steven Poole", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Facilities Manager at The Rhodes Trust - Oxford University", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stevenpoole/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADWAL8BiNLjb-fjy1wyRALA-lyGXh0wJMM", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Kelly was senior to Adelaide but didn't manage Adelaide directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "October 31, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Dynamic and results-oriented, Kelly is a great GM that has the ability to bring his team to the best. It was a pleasure to work with him.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Adelaide Castano", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Owner at Soul Phuket", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adelaide-castano-31489a17/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAODLkABwosSSi3MiK_L3pyRVhLOJrsEZTQ", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Kelly was François's client", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "July 3, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I was starting to set up my company \"Big Waves of Inspiration\" and I presented to Kelly my program on \"Managing Perception\". Straight away he beleived in the idea and gave me the opportunity to test my program with 8 hotel General Managers in Phuket and with his management team at Indigo Pearl. Since I was able to run a full day program for his top management team and we are working on scheduling another session in the upcoming month in Phuket.\nI was very much inspired by the amount of passion and energy Kelly is showing to his team, customers and owners. He is on a very exciting mission to make Indigo Pearl Phuket a very unique and special place in Phuket. While He has a clear vision for his resort, he is giving himself, his team, his employees every chances to achieve it.\nI am very thankful grateful to Kelly and Indigo Pearl for giving the chance to run my first program and looking forward working together again.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "François Huet", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "🎙️ Auteur du podcast Xperientiel | 🌱 Producteur de podcasts engagés | 🤝 Facilitateur de transitions écologiques et humaines", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/françois-huet-a6527a14/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALjGG0BW1l_2Bc0PwwZiXw9Ev1rD3aBFl8", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Matt reported directly to Kelly", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "March 31, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I got the chance to have Kelly mentor me and he was the most influencial leader I have ever worked with.  He helped guide me along my path in Revenue Management and really got the ball rolling for me.  Kelly generally cares about everyone that works for him and always has time to stop and ask you how you are doing.  Kelly was by far the most professional and hardest working individual I have ever done business with.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Matt Thomas", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Global Pricing Director", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mpthomas1219/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAARTzoABv-N5iAJt6FrfK0gER3ghTdkXxOA", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Peter worked with Kelly on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "February 8, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Kelly joined the Hotel Victor shortly after I was appointed its Asset Manager. His knowledge of the business and his ability to totally comprehend the opportunities that lay within the property's P&L made our partnership so much more workable. Together we were able to make significant improvements, though it was Kelly's keen eye for standards and luxury values that kept the Hotel Victor in the upper echelons of all hotels in the South Beach market - despite the downturn that the recent recession caused. His ability to personally select only the most passionate employees to join his team was a credit to him.", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Peter Hilary", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Resort Management | Hotel Operations | Employee Management | Managerial/Administrative Support | Strategic Planning | Hospitality Management | Team Leadership/Training | Operational Management | Revenue Generation", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/peter-hilary-59796722/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAATE5IMBchI03m3z6T86W3SoAc-94Eve554", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Michael reported directly to Kelly", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendationsR