at seeks highly creative and top performing Executive Chef.", "recommendations/0/name": "Gael Lardiere", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Cluster Director of Food And Beverage / Pre-Opening Specialist", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gael-lardiere-8926a2/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAaBG4Bnu9TDv_bGzyo-4jVLX-WgBeP2jI", "recommendations/1/context": "Devan managed Samney directly", "recommendations/1/date": "October 17, 2011", "recommendations/1/description": "Samney was the right candidate as Concierge and he did it well with trainings and setups we successfully open the Victoria Angkor. He is very hands on and works long hours to ensure smooth service and guest requests are handled and complete. I strongly recommend him to any hotels seeking a young and experience and also an all rounder FOM.", "recommendations/1/name": "Samney Sin", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "General Manager | ibis budget Phnom Penh Riverside", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/samney-sin-5990b537/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAeq0AUBVWI_AxNVbLO5rPmqGl6ZhsSbVwo", "recommendations/2/context": "Devan was Pon's client", "recommendations/2/date": "June 10, 2010", "recommendations/2/name": "Pon BUTH-ប៊ុត ប៉ុន", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Hub Leader-Market Expansion and Business Growth Strategy | Ex. Expedia Group (Cambodia-Laos-Pakistan) | Ex. General Manager-Pre-Opening (Hotels&Resorts) | Ex. Belmond La Residence d’Angkor | Ex. Victoria Group | More..", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pon-buth-ប៊ុត-ប៉ុន-6b294821/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASWueYBnNzDlDzFBg7p4zO7dml5HGA7JNM", "skills/0/title": "Pre opening", "skills/1/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/2/title": "Resort", "skills/3/title": "Re Opening", "skills/4/title": "Re Branding", "skills/5/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/6/title": "Hotels", "skills/7/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/8/title": "Resorts", "skills/9/title": "Yield Management", "skills/10/title": "Rebranding", "skills/11/title": "Micros", "skills/12/title": "Hospitality Industry", "skills/13/title": "Front Office", "skills/14/title": "Revenue Analysis", "skills/15/title": "Hospitality", "skills/16/title": "Opera", "skills/17/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/18/title": "Property Management Systems", "skills/19/title": "Budgets", "totalExperienceYears": "12.5", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "3", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "0", "updates/0/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E12AQFZvEKU0z6nzw/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/0/1520095293904?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=BT4LCDK3p95h7jkvnl_wbK0VHEqGZaVJbjVmCjrX1Lk", "updates/0/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/racha-many-guests-never-want-leave-dont-devan-bhaskaran", "updates/0/postText": "Many of our guests tell us that memories of The Racha stay on with them, long after they depart. Season after season, our staff delight in welcoming familiar faces back to our island resort. Some guests return for the care and friendship of the staff. Others to indulge again in the resort’s many creature comforts - from basking in sunlit ozonated pools, to enjoying The Racha’s eco-chic villas and strolling the resort’s twenty acre grounds. Many guests return to soak in the beauty and magic of Racha Yai island, rated as one of the Andaman Sea’s most beautiful. At The Racha, when we say “we hope to see you soon again” to our guests, we often we do. www.theracha.com.", "updates/0/subTitle": "At the Racha, many guests never want to leave.  and they don’t.", "updates/0/title": "At the Racha, many guests never want to leave.  and they don’t.", "updates/0/type": "Article", "updates/1/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E12AQHETBVHOdXRcA/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/0/1520204037687?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=5rVPSxHZLyJ23f1AZF9DgwIeM5cDvNfC8eU_tHV3gz8", "updates/1/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/we-grow-our-own-greens-racha-devan-bhaskaran", "updates/1/postText": "Hydroponic growing is the best way to overcome global food and water shortages and produce the highest quality, nutritious produce in any type of climate. The Racha started its own hydroponic plant for fresh salad greens. We harvest Green and Red Oak, Red Coral, Romaine, Butter Head, Iceberg and Cos Romaine(mini). Fresh salads anyone...", "updates/1/subTitle": "We Grow Our Own Greens At The Racha.", "updates/1/title": "We Grow Our Own Greens At The Racha.", "updates/1/type": "Article", "updates/2/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E12AQGCHdNcDGrjmw/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/0/1520164895147?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=UjxI_1jquJtLTWYI3n4p_rP3ytyD2VaP8Mz1MfXS3Fk", "updates/2/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/racha-environmental-practice-devan-bhaskaran", "updates/2/postText": "250 KWp Solar Diesel Hybrid project (first of its kind in South East Asia) – this will significantly reduce our carbon emissions by harnessing the Sun’s energy to provide up to 50% of the resort’s power demands during daylight hours. Our environment is everywhere around us and if we do not take care of it today, who will take care of it tomorrow for us? It is our responsibility to safe-guard our environment for our future generations and this responsibility starts today!", "updates/2/subTitle": "The Racha - Environmental Practice", "updates/2/title": "The Racha - Environmental Practice", "updates/2/type": "Article", "urn": "ACoAAALy7HoBLQ6Hid6A5Be0ZOiC32kT_G07hp0"}$$::jsonb);